  <steps>
    <step num="0">In a large pan or wok, heat the oil over high. Fry the string beans until they start blistering. Remove the string beans. </step>
    <step num="1">In the same pan or wok, add the garlic, ginger, and scallions. Fry until fragrant. </step>
    <step num="2">Add the mushrooms and ground pork. Fry until the pork is mostly done. Stir in the the dried red chilies and chili paste. </step>
    <step num="3">Add the string beans back the pan/wok. Toss to combine everything. Add the soy sauce, rice wine, and a dash of white pepper. Serve! </step>
    <step num="4">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
